UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304405X0200140X
KW  - Performance evaluation
KW  - Pension funds
KW  - Conditioning
KW  - Portfolio weights
AB  - This paper combines the use of portfolio holdings data and conditioning information to create a new performance measure. Our conditional weight-based measure has several advantages. Using conditioning information avoids biases in weight-based measures as discussed by Grinblatt and Titman (J. Business 60 (1993)). When conditioning information is used, returns-based measures face a bias if managers can trade between observation dates. The new measures avoid this interim trading bias. We use the new measures to provide fresh insights about performance in a sample of U.S. equity pension fund managers.
ER  - 
